content:
The Set Values action sets values in the data JSON of an Integration Procedure literally, using merge fields, or using formulas. This action has many uses.

To create the Integration Procedure, go to the Vlocity Integration Procedures tab and click New. Provide an Integration Procedure Name, a Type, and a SubType, and click Save.

The input data has the following structure:

{
    "Name": {
        "FirstName": "John",
        "LastName": "Smith"
    },
    "Finances": {
        "GrossIncome": "100000",
        "Expenses": "60000"
    }
}

Inputs: Rename Nodes in the Input Data

This component shortens and simplifies the input data. LocationData: Add Literal Values

This component adds literal values, which are useful for testing or for specifying data that doesn't change.

TextWithCode: Concatenate Literal Values and Merge Fields

This component shows how to concatenate a literal string with a merge field. DeptArray: Define an Array

This component defines an array, or list of values.

AfterTax and CalculateNet: Perform Simple Calculations Using Formulas

These components calculate after-tax income using multiplication and net income using subtraction.

ConcatName: Concatenate Two Merge Fields

This component combines first and last names to form full names.

RetrieveDept: Use a Function and Retrieving an Array Value

This component uses the IF function. It also uses listnode|listnumber notation to retrieve array values.

CalcFirstOfThisMonth: Perform a Complex Date Calculation

This component uses four nested date functions to return the first day of the current month.

AssembleOutput: Create the Structure of the Output Data

This component creates a JSON structure for the transformed data. Response: Return the Output Data

This component returns the output data to the entity that called the Integration Procedure.

Test the Integration Procedure that Sets Values
title: Configuring Set Values in OmniStudio
